President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Arkansas due to severe storms and flooding that occurred between December 23, 2009, and January 2, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be provided on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The designated areas include several counties in Arkansas. Kevin L. Hannes has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.